This paper discusses the design and implementation of a bio-inspired robot capable of homeostasis, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence in creating a robot that can regulate its internal environment (cs.AI). The robot's ability to maintain internal parameters and defend itself from the environment involves control systems and sensors, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the mechanical design of the robot, which involves the use of wheels, making it relevant to the field of mechanical engineering (cs.ME). Finally, the paper is inspired by biological systems, making it relevant to the field of bioinformatics (cs.BIO).
